com.mostc.pftt.results
Class PhptTestResult

java.lang.Object
  com.mostc.pftt.results.PhptTestResult

public class PhptTestResult
extends java.lang.Object

result of running a PhptTestCase the status of PhptTestCase is determined by: -executing SKIPIF section(optional) -comparing the actual and EXPECT, EXPECTF or EXPECTREGEX sections -certain sections are skipped for HTTP testing

Author:
Matt Ficken

regex_compiler_dump

public java.lang.String regex_compiler_dump
if FAIL or XFAIL_WORKS and has an EXPECTF or EXPECTREGEX section, this will be the debug output from the regular expression compiler. There may have been an error handling the EXPECTF/EXPECTREGEX section (so FAIL or XFAIL_WORKS may be a PFTT bug), and this output may help.

regex_output

public java.lang.String regex_output
if FAIL or XFAIL_WORKS and has an EXPECTF or EXPECTREGEX section, this will be the debug output of matching done by the regular expression engine.
